-- Author:    James H. Hill
--
-- $Id: README 956 2006-12-05 22:09:03Z hillj $
--
-- CUTS baseline benchmark service for the Benchmark Data Collector.
-- This service collects metrics for a single component over a period
-- of time by monitoring the activity of its ports. When the service
-- is notified of new metrics, it accumulates them with the metrics
-- of the previous collection periods. Once the service is deactivated,
-- it stores the accumulated metrics to a database as a baseline metric
-- for that component.
===============================================================================

USAGE: CUTS_Baseline_Service [OPTIONS]

Benchmark options:
  -d, --default-baseline,     default basline metric for component on
                              all hosts
  -w, --warmup-count=VALUE    number of collections to ingore due to
                              system warmup; default is 1

Database options:
  --server=VALUE              location of the database; default is
                              'localhost'

Miscellaneous:
  --verbose                   print information about progress
